You are working in a Next.js 16 project with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, and shadcn/ui.

## Project Structure
- App Router (not Pages Router)
- `src/app/(app)/` — pages with sidebar layout (dashboard, settings, etc.)
- `src/app/` — standalone pages (landing, auth, etc.)
- `src/components/ui/` — shadcn/ui primitives (pre-installed, don't recreate)
- `src/components/layout/` — layout components (sidebar, topbar)
- `src/components/` — shared feature components
- `src/hooks/` — custom hooks (useLocalStorage, useMediaQuery, useDebounce, useIsMobile)
- `src/lib/utils.ts` — cn() utility for className merging

## Rules
1. Use ONLY Tailwind CSS utility classes for styling. Never create CSS modules, styled-components, or inline style objects.
2. Use the existing shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui/` — they are ALL pre-installed. Never recreate or duplicate them.
3. Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional classNames.
4. Use design system tokens defined in `globals.css`: `primary`, `secondary`, `muted`, `accent`, `destructive`, `brand`, `success`, `warning`, `info`.
5. Use `lucide-react` for icons. Import like: `import { IconName } from "lucide-react"`.
6. Use Framer Motion for animations. Import like: `import { motion } from "framer-motion"`.
7. Use `"use client"` directive only when the component needs hooks, event handlers, or browser APIs. Default to server components.
8. For toasts: `import { toast } from "sonner"` then `toast.success("message")`.
9. For forms: use React Hook Form + Zod with shadcn Form components.
10. New app pages with sidebar go in `src/app/(app)/your-route/page.tsx`.
11. New standalone pages go in `src/app/your-route/page.tsx`.
12. Always add `loading.tsx` alongside pages that fetch data.
13. Use path aliases: `@/components`, `@/lib`, `@/hooks`, `@/app`.
14. File naming: kebab-case for files, PascalCase for components, camelCase for hooks/utils.
15. When adding nav items, update `src/components/layout/app-sidebar.tsx`.
16. Keep components focused and small. Compose from shadcn/ui primitives.
17. Use TypeScript strict mode. Type all props and avoid `any`.
18. For data fetching, prefer server components with async/await or server actions.

## Available Hooks
- `useLocalStorage(key, initialValue)` — persist state in localStorage
- `useMediaQuery(query)` — responsive breakpoint detection
- `useDebounce(value, delay)` — debounce rapidly changing values
- `useIsMobile()` — detect mobile viewport

## Available Libraries (already installed)
- next, react, react-dom
- tailwindcss v4, shadcn/ui (all components)
- lucide-react (icons)
- framer-motion (animations)
- next-themes (dark mode)
- sonner (toasts)
- react-hook-form, @hookform/resolvers, zod (forms + validation)
- recharts (charts)
- date-fns (date utilities)
- cmdk (command palette)
- embla-carousel-react (carousels)
- react-resizable-panels (resizable layouts)
- vaul (drawers)

Read CONVENTIONS.md for full project structure and patterns.
